<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <%- include('components/meta') %>
    <title>Document</title>
    <script src="js/index.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1 class="fit-width">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="64" height="64" fill="currentColor" id="gh-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
                <path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.012 8.012 0 0 0 16 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"/>
            </svg>
            Github Follow Recommendations
        </h1>        
    </header>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row" id="mainRow">
            <div class="col fit-width" id="mainForm">
                <br>
                <div>Enter your Github username</div>
                <form action = "user">
                    <input name="username" type="txt" value="<%=username%>">
                    <div>Select degrees of separation</div>
                    <select name="depth">
                        <option value="1">1</option>
                        <option value="2" selected>2</option>
                        <option value="3">3</option>
                    </select>
                    <br><br>
                    <input type="submit" onclick="startLoading()">
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row" id="footer">
            <h3>About</h3>
            <p class="dim-color">
            Enter your username and see other GitHub users you 
            might know based on mutual followers / following.
            The degrees of separation are how many followers down the chain these people are.
            At degree 1, it only shows your immediately connections (followers and following). 
            At degree 2, it shows the following and followers of the degree 1 users. At degree 3, it shows degree 2, plus their connections.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <%- include('components/loading') %>
</body>
</html>